# Subjects' Connection

# First Episode
										Bir cümle bitirilene kadar, bu kısım kendini arka arkaya kopyalayabilir.
						modal verb			------------------------------------------------------------------------------
		(noun/pronoun)			verb + verb (gerund/infinitive)				(noun/pronoun)
		subject				verb (tenses)			preposition		object 		/	adjective	/	adverb		conjunction
🟣		🔴 ---------------------------- 🔴 ---------------------------- 🔵 ------------------- 🔵 ----------------------------------------------------		🟣

																					
						modal verb - yardımcı fiil												conjunction - bağlaç (iki cümleyi bağlar)
		   noun - isim			gerund (V + Ving)											adverb - zarf (fiili niteler)
		pronoun - zamir			infinitive (V to V)								adjective - sıfat (ismi niteler)
		subject - özne (eylemi yapan)	verb - fiil, eylem		preposition - edat	object - nesne (eyleme maruz kalan)
										(iki kelimeyi bağlar)




			time		 + 	aspects										= tenses
			----------------------------------------------- eylem / fiil / yüklem -----------------------------------------------------------------------
			past			simple			(standart/rutin olur)					options/combinations to express/speak			
			present			continuous 		(bir müddet devam eder)
			future			perfect 		(tamamlanmış ama etkisi zamana göre devam eder)
						perfect continuous	(etkisi de, kendisi de devam eder)




			12 options to express
			---------------------
			'past	 simple tense'		'past	 continuous tense'		'past 	 perfect tense'		'past	 perfect continuous tense'
			'present simple tense'		'present continuous tense'		'present perfect tense'		'present perfect continuous tense'
			'future	 simple tense'		'future	 continuous tense'		'future  perfect tense'		'future  perfect continuous tense'



			5 options  to speak
			-------------------
			Present Simple 		-ar, -er	(Geniş zaman)		you watch us			they see him
			Present Continuous	-iyor		(Şimdiki zaman)		you are watching us 		they are seeing him

											you are going to watch us	they are going to see him
			Future Simple		-acak, -ecek	(Gelecek Zaman)		you will watch us		they will see him

			Present Perfect		-dı, -di	(Türkçede yok)		he has watched us	they have seen him
			Past Simple		-dı, -di	(Geçmiş zaman)		he watched us		they saw him





# Second Episode

										ACTIVE VOICE
										(Etken Çatı)
		------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

		▫️▫️▫️						▫️▫️▫️					▫️▫️▫️
		past perfect continuous				past continuous (-iyordu)		present perfect continuous
		#						#					#						 (-iyor..)
Tenses		past perfect (-mış,-miş)			past simple (-dı,-di)			present perfect (-dı,-di)		present continuous ----------|---> be going to
		🔴～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～ 🔴 ----------------------------------- 🔴～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～ 🔵 - - - - - - - - - -> FUTURE (-acak, -ecek)
		1. Verb						2. Verb										      	  |------> will

		|						|					|					|
		|	PERFECT					|	PAST				|	PRESENT				|
Modals		|	MODALS					|	MODALS				|	MODALS				|
		|	could  have V3				|	could  V1			|	can 	V1			|
		|	would  have V3				|	would  V1			|	will 	V1 (future simple)	|
		|	might  have V3				|	might  V1			|	may	V1			|
		|	should have V3				|	should V1			|	shall	V1			|			
		|	must   have V3				|					|	must	V1			|
		|						|					|					|
		|						|					|					|

Conditionals	type 3 (Impossible)				type 2 (Less Possible)			type 1 (Possible)			type 0 (Certain)
                If + Past Perfect / 				If + Past Simple /			If + Present Time, Present Modal	If + Present Simple, Present Simple
		     Past Perfect Continuous, perfect modal	     Past Continuous, Past Modal		










